4.Your rights
You have the right to request us to provide a copy of your personal information in accordance with national/regional laws; Correct, delete or restrict your personal information.
In addition, in some cases, you may object to the processing of your personal information (in particular, we do not need to process the information to meet contractual or other legal requirements, or we use the information for direct marketing).
These rights may be limited, for example, if you disclose a person's personal information request, or if you require us to delete or force us to retain information of legitimate interest (for example, to prevent fraud).
5.How to protect your information
Your personal information is contained behind a secure network and is accessible only to a small number of people with access to such systems and requires confidential information. In addition, all sensitive credit information you provide is encrypted by technology.
When you use the application in any way, we implement various security measures to maintain the security of your personal information.
6.How to store your information
Whenever necessary, we retain the information we collect in accordance with this Privacy Policy to meet our business or operational purposes or to comply with legal requirements. We can also choose to analyze some of the information we collect so that it can no longer be identified or attributed to anyone if we want to keep it for a longer period of time.
